<h3 id="headers">Headers</h3>

<p>It is important to think about the structure of content on a page before choosing the appropriate heading. It is not about choosing one that looks nice, rather think about where the heading fits into the overall content hierarchy so that it makes sense.</p>

<p>Keep the implementation consistent across the entire site to maximise usability.</p>

<p>Do not skip headings in the structure e.g. going from heading 2 to heading 4.</p>

<ul>
	<li>There must be only one <code>h1</code> element on a page: the heading University of St Andrews; <code>h1</code> must not be used anywhere else on the page.</li>
	<li>You may use as many <code>h2</code> elements as required to denote new sections on a page.</li>
	<li>You may use as many <code>h3</code> to <code>h4</code> elements as required to denote sub-sections of content on a page.</li>
	<li>You must not use <code>h5</code> or <code>h6</code> elements.</li>
	</ul>

