<h3 id="body-text">Body text</h3>

<ul>
	<li>The <code>p</code> tag defines a paragraph.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Bold and strong</h4>
<ul>	
	<li>The HTML <code>b</code> element defines <b>bold</b> text, without any extra importance.</li>
		<li>The HTML <code>strong</code> element defines <strong>strong</strong> text, with added semantic "strong" importance.</li>
	<li>Try to keep items in bold and strong as short as possible and refrain from writing entire sentences or paragraphs in a bold or strong typeface.</li>
	<li>Bold and strong text should not be used as a substitute for headings.</li>
</ul>	

<h4>Italics and emphasis</h4>
<ul>	
	<li>The HTML <code>i</code> element defines <i>italic</i> text, without any extra importance.</li>
	<li>The HTML <code>em</code> element defines <em>emphasized</em> text, with added semantic importance.</li>
	<li>For accessibility reasons, avoid the excessive use of italics and emphasis on the web.</li>
</ul>


