<h3 id="attr">Abbreviated text</h3>

<p>The <code>abbr</code> tag is used to define an abbreviation or an acronym. This can give useful information to browser, translation systems, and search engines.</p>

<p>By deafult in desktop browsers the <code>abbr</code> tag provides a tooltip mouseover.</p>

<p>Please note, <code>abbr</code> tags are redundent on mobile browsers. In which case it is recommended to write it out abbreviations and acronyms in full, e.g. World Health Organisation (WHO).</p>

